                    <p>...</p>
                    
                </div>
                
            </div>	
            
            <div type="commentary">	
                
                <p>The three portions of this inscription are possibly the continuation or a supplement to the inscription preceding them on the wall, that is, <ref target="DHARMA_INSTiruvavatuturai10003.xml">Tiruvavāṭutuṟai 3</ref> (ARIE/1924-1925/B/1925/111).</p>
                <p>The 29th year of an unmentioned king is found in the first portion. This unmentioned king might be the Rājarāja mentioned in the same first portion.</p>
                
            </div>
            
            <div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Possibly reported in <bibl><ptr target="bib:ARIE1924-1925"/></bibl> as part of ARIE/1924-1925/B/1925/111.</p>	
